<div id="review_1356717500" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1356717500" />
    <a title="Paul E. Morph" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44824883-paul-e-morph"><img alt="Paul E. Morph" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611008105p2/44824883.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1356717500?book_show_action=true">Oct 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul E. Morph" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul E. Morph" href="/user/show/44824883-paul-e-morph">Paul E. Morph</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19098531-earthly-powers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44824883-paul-e-morph?shelf=books-read-in-2019">books-read-in-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1356717500" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer412964248066294201">This chunky doorstop is an excellent novel that explores the nature of art, family, sexuality, power, authority, violence, illness, love, language and religion. Essentially, I think it&apos;s about the nature of humanity, and is very much a &apos;warts-and-all&apos; delving into the subject.<br/><br/>I really enjoyed this one and was gripped all the way through. I&apos;d give it five stars but, if I&apos;m totally honest with myself, there were definitely moments I found... annoying.<br/><br/>Despite that; great book!</span>
  <span id="freeText412964248066294201" style="display:none">This chunky doorstop is an excellent novel that explores the nature of art, family, sexuality, power, authority, violence, illness, love, language and religion. Essentially, I think it's about the nature of humanity, and is very much a 'warts-and-all' delving into the subject.<br /><br />I really enjoyed this one and was gripped all the way through. I'd give it five stars but, if I'm totally honest with myself, there were definitely moments I found... annoying.<br /><br />Despite that; great book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="412964248066294201" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


